DataGrid

Takes a list of entities, a model, and renders a table. The model displays the raw value unles you pass it a Component The model support custom menu for table header

  <DataGrid
    useSmartOverflowX
    resizable
    reorderable
    propertyKey="name"
    selectable
    onInvertSelection={selected => {
      console.log('datagrid.mdx onInvertSelection', selected)

    onSelectionChange={(isSelected, entityId, selected) => {
      console.log(
        'isSelected, entityId, selected',
        isSelected,
        entityId,
        selected,
      )
    }}
    onSelectAllChange={selectAllChecked => {
      console.log('selectAllChecked', selectAllChecked)
    }}
    model={[
      {
        property: 'firstName',
        displayName: 'First name',
        CellDetail: entity => {
          return (

              </Flex>
              <div>
                <a href="#">View original</a>
              </div>
              <div>
                <a href="#">Search for similar</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          )
        },
        // Component,
        menuDescriptor: [
          {
            label: 'foo',
            icon: <Circle />,
            onClick: () => {
              console.log('foo')
            },
            children: [
              {
                label: 'bar',
                icon: <Circle />,
                onClick: () => {
                  console.log('foo>bar')
                },
              },

<ThemeProvider>
  <WithState
    defaultState={{
      selected: ['bar', 'vrn'],
      sortDirections: [
        { property: 'name' },
        { property: 'firstName', sortDirection: 'ASC' },
      ],
    }}
  >
    {(state, setState) => (
      <DataGrid
        useSmartOverflowX
        resizable
        reorderable
        propertyKey="name"
        selectable
        multiSelectable
        selected={state.selected}
        onInvertSelection={selected => {
          console.log('datagrid.mdx onInvertSelection', selected)
          setState({ ...state, selected })
        }}
        onSelectionChange={(isSelected, entityId, selected) => {
          console.log(
            'isSelected, entityId, selected',
            isSelected,
            entityId,
            selected,
          )
          setState({ ...state, selected })
        }}
        onSelectAllChange={selectAllChecked => {
          console.log('selectAllChecked', selectAllChecked)
          setState({
            ...state,
            selected: selectAllChecked
              ? [
                  { age: 123, firstName: 'foo', name: 'bar' },
                  { age: 123, firstName: 'baz', name: 'foo' },
                  { age: 123, firstName: 'fuz', name: 'fob' },
                  { age: 123, firstName: 'voo', name: 'mar' },
                  { age: 123, firstName: 'bop', name: 'vrn' },
                ].map(({ name }) => name)
              : [],
          })
        }}
        model={[
          {
            property: 'firstName',
            displayName: 'First name',
            CellDetail: entity => {
              return (
                <div style={{ padding: '16px' }}>
                  <h4>Valid Data</h4>
                  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet</p>
                  <Flex
                    style={{ justifyContent: 'flex-start', margin: '8px 0' }}
                  >
                    <Circle style={{ margin: '0 8px' }} />
                    <Circle style={{ margin: '0 8px' }} />
                  </Flex>
                  <div>
                    <a href="#">View original</a>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <a href="#">Search for similar</a>
                  </div>
                </div>
              )
            },
            // Component,
            menuDescriptor: [
              {
                label: 'foo',
                icon: <Circle />,
                onClick: () => {
                  console.log('foo')
                },
                children: [
                  {
                    label: 'bar',
                    icon: <Circle />,
                    onClick: () => {
                      console.log('foo>bar')
                    },
                  },
                  {
                    label: 'foo',
                    icon: <Circle />,
                    onClick: () => {
                      console.log('foo>bar')
                    },
                    children: [
                      {
                        label: 'bar',
                        icon: <Circle />,
                        onClick: () => {
                          console.log('foo>bar')
                        },
                      },
                      {
                        label: 'foo',
                        icon: <Circle />,
                        onClick: () => {
                          console.log('foo>bar')
                        },
                      },
                    ],
                  },
                ],
              },
              {
                label: 'bar',
                icon: <Circle />,
                onClick: () => {
                  console.log('foo')
                },
              },
            ],
          },
          // { property: 'name', displayName: 'Name', menu: <ButtonMenu button={'≡'}>yooooo</ButtonMenu> },
          {
            property: 'name',
            displayName: 'Name',
            menu: (
              <Flex style={{ padding: '8px', marginLeft: 'auto' }}>
                <Star />
              </Flex>
            ),
          },
          {
            property: 'age',
            displayName: 'Age',
            menuDescriptor: [
              {
                label: 'foo',
                icon: <Circle />,
                onClick: () => {
                  console.log('foo')
                },
                children: [
                  {
                    label: 'bar',
                    icon: <Circle />,
                    onClick: () => {
                      console.log('foo>bar')
                    },
                  },
                ],
                // type: ,
                // Link: ,
                // to: ,
                // href: ,
                // target: ,
                // isFullWidth: ,
              },
            ],
          },
        ]}
        data={[
          {
            age: 123,
            firstName: 'foozefv ojnzfkgjnbzjrnvzoekrjnv',
            name: 'bar',
          },
          {
            age: 123,
            firstName: 'baz kzejfnvlskngd bl lknf lkzfn g',
            name: 'foo',
          },
          { age: 123, firstName: 'fuz', name: 'fob' },
          { age: 123, firstName: 'voo', name: 'mar' },
          {
            age: 123,
            firstName:
              'boplkznfknlfjgnkjnzfjkleznlfnzekjrfnkzenrkzejrnkzejrnf',
            name: 'vrn',
          },
        ]}
        sortable
        sortDirections={state.sortDirections}
        defaultSortDirections={undefined}
        onSortChange={(property, sortDirection, newSortDirections) => {
          console.log('mdx: newSortDirections', newSortDirections)
          setState({ ...state, sortDirections: newSortDirections })
        }}
        // tableHeaderOverlayRender={(data) => {
        //   console.log('data', data)

        //     <Flex

<ThemeProvider>
  <DataGrid
    model={[
      {
        property: 'name',
        displayName: 'Name',
      },
      {
        property: 'roles',
        displayName: 'User groups',
        Component: entity =>
          entity.roles.map((r, i, { length }) => (
            <div>
              <i>{r}</i>
              {i === length - 1 ? '' : ', '}
            </div>
          )),
      },
    ]}
    data={[{ name: 'John', roles: ['admin', 'editor', 'writer'] }]}
  />
</ThemeProvider>
